{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623145","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623145"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:08:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:08:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16836"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16836","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16836"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.87,0.04,0.02,0.04,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9526"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107541"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9526"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16836"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90011"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"106"},{"type":"tags","id":"182"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5003"},{"type":"tags","id":"5009"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22505"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22511"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39967"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107541"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman is diagnosed with new onset atrial fibrillation. She has no history of valvular heart disease or recent surgery. Her CHA2DS2-VASc score is 4.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate indication for factor Xa inhibitor therapy in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Prevention of stroke in non-valvular atrial fibrillation","Prevention of mechanical valve thrombosis","Treatment of acute coronary syndrome","Rhythm control of atrial fibrillation","Treatment of heparin-induced thrombocytopenia"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate indication is \u003Cstrong\u003Eprevention of stroke in non-valvular atrial fibrillation\u003C/strong\u003E. This patient has a CHA2DS2-VASc score indicating significant stroke risk, and direct oral anticoagulants are the first-line option for stroke prevention in this setting. Direct oral anticoagulants include factor Xa inhibitors (apixaban, rivaroxaban) and direct thrombin inhibitors (dabigatran) are the first-line option for stroke prevention in this setting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFactor Xa inhibitors are contraindicated in patients with mechanical heart valves, making \u003Cstrong\u003Eprevention of mechanical valve thrombosis\u003C/strong\u003E an inappropriate choice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of acute coronary syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E requires antiplatelet therapy, and factor Xa inhibitors alone are not indicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERhythm control of atrial fibrillation \u003C/strong\u003Eis not a therapeutic action of factor Xa inhibitors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of heparin-induced thrombocytopenia\u003C/strong\u003E requires direct thrombin inhibitors as the preferred therapeutic option.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFactor Xa inhibitors are also commonly used for treatment and prevention of venous thromboembolism, but stroke prevention in non-valvular atrial fibrillation is a major indication.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Direct oral anticoagulants are first line for prevention of stroke in non-valvular atrial fibrillation.","A CHA2DS2-VASc of \u22652 for males or \u22653 for females warrants commencement of anticoagulation in the setting of atrial fibrillation.","Factor Xa inhibitors are contraindicated in patients with mechanical heart valves."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Lip GY, Nieuwlaat R, Pisters R, Lane DA, Crijns HJ. Refining clinical risk stratification for predicting stroke and thromboembolism in atrial fibrillation using a novel risk factor-based approach: the euro heart survey on atrial fibrillation. Chest. 2010;137(2):263-272. doi:10.1378/chest.09-1584","Clinical Excellence Commission. DOAC Guidelines Direct Oral Anticoagulants [Internet]. 2023. Available from: https://www.cec.health.nsw.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/917807/DOAC-guidelines.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90011"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16836"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90011"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-01T09:10:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-01T09:11:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9526"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107541"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"ta